President Barack Obama has proclaimed November 21 to November 27, 2010, as National Family Week in the United States. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of families in building vibrant communities and a strong nation. The Obama administration is committed to finding solutions to the issues affecting American families, such as economic security and access to healthcare. The Affordable Care Act and the Health Care and Education Reconciliation Act are mentioned as significant steps in strengthening health security and providing support for families. The president also acknowledges the sacrifices of service members and their families during the holiday season. He calls on all states, local communities, and individuals to observe National Family Week with appropriate ceremonies and activities to honor families.